    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but i've been reading online that garlic actually works as a natural blood thinner and is much safer for your stomach than the pills. if i slowly tapered off the warfarin and just started taking like 2000mg of garlic extract a day and drank a green juice every morning, would that work to keep my levels steady? i really want to avoid the doctor visits if possible.",
